Now I'll execute the first tool in the workflow to read the input data. I'll use the default file path as specified in the environment rules.

<tool_call>file_operations_reader
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the parser tool to process the data we just read. Since the parser requires a source, I'll use the same input file path as the reader tool.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the filter tool to complete the data transformation pipeline. Since it doesn't require any specific parameters, I'll use the default empty options.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
